main event: Ground radar at Dover AFB, Delaware detected two unidentified objects on 9th November 1955, lasting for 2-3 minutes. Military and civilian personnel were involved in the observation.
interesting points: The objects were sighted on radar and then lost to radar, with unknown altitude and a duration of 2-3 minutes.
The conclusion stated that it was not a balloon, but possibly an aircraft, indicating uncertainty about the nature of the objects.
The document contains a description of an unusual event involving a 'ball' and 'bat-shape' object at 32,000 ft, with specific details about their movements and appearance.
The report also mentions a separate visual observation of a brilliant metallic object hovering over Little Creek, Delaware, at an altitude of 7'11'', involving ground and air force personnel.
The sighting report includes references to jettisoned balloons and launched balloons from Dover AFB, adding complexity to the investigation.
sighted object: Two unidentified objects detected on ground radar, and a brilliant metallic object hovering over Little Creek, Delaware.
witnesses: Military and civilian personnel, ground and air force personnel
